43class spell_gen_absorb0_hitlimit1 : public SpellScriptLoader
44{
45 public:
46 spell_gen_absorb0_hitlimit1() : SpellScriptLoader("spell_gen_absorb0_hitlimit1") { }
47
48 class spell_gen_absorb0_hitlimit1_AuraScript : public AuraScript
49 {
50 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_absorb0_hitlimit1_AuraScript);
51
52 public:
53 spell_gen_absorb0_hitlimit1_AuraScript()
54 {
55 limit = 0;
56 }
57
58 private:
59 uint32 limit;
60
61 bool Load() override
62 {
63 // Max absorb stored in 1 dummy effect
64 limit = GetSpellInfo()->GetEffect(EFFECT_1)->CalcValue();
65 return true;
66 }
67
68 void Absorb(AuraEffect* /*aurEff*/, DamageInfo& /*dmgInfo*/, uint32& absorbAmount)
69 {
70 absorbAmount = std::min(limit, absorbAmount);
71 }
72
73 void Register() override
74 {
75 OnEffectAbsorb += AuraEffectAbsorbFn(spell_gen_absorb0_hitlimit1_AuraScript::Absorb, EFFECT_0);
76 }
77 };
78
79 AuraScript* GetAuraScript() const override
80 {
81 return new spell_gen_absorb0_hitlimit1_AuraScript();
82 }

95class spell_gen_adaptive_warding : public SpellScriptLoader
96{
97 public:
98 spell_gen_adaptive_warding() : SpellScriptLoader("spell_gen_adaptive_warding") { }
99
100 class spell_gen_adaptive_warding_AuraScript : public AuraScript
101 {
102 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_adaptive_warding_AuraScript);
103
104 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
105 {
106 if (!sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_FIRE) ||
107 !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_NATURE) ||
108 !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_FROST) ||
109 !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_SHADOW) ||
110 !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_ARCANE))
111 return false;
112 return true;
113 }
114
115 bool CheckProc(ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
116 {
117 if (eventInfo.GetDamageInfo()->GetSpellInfo()) // eventInfo.GetSpellInfo()
118 return false;
119
120 // find Mage Armor
121 if (!GetTarget()->GetAuraEffect(SPELL_AURA_MOD_MANA_REGEN_INTERRUPT, SPELLFAMILY_MAGE, flag128(0x10000000, 0x0, 0x0)))
122 return false;
123
124 switch (GetFirstSchoolInMask(eventInfo.GetSchoolMask()))
125 {
126 case SPELL_SCHOOL_NORMAL:
127 case SPELL_SCHOOL_HOLY:
128 return false;
129 default:
130 break;
131 }
132 return true;
133 }
134
135 void HandleProc(AuraEffect const* aurEff, ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
136 {
137 PreventDefaultAction();
138
139 uint32 spellId = 0;
140 switch (GetFirstSchoolInMask(eventInfo.GetSchoolMask()))
141 {
142 case SPELL_SCHOOL_FIRE:
143 spellId = SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_FIRE;
144 break;
145 case SPELL_SCHOOL_NATURE:
146 spellId = SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_NATURE;
147 break;
148 case SPELL_SCHOOL_FROST:
149 spellId = SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_FROST;
150 break;
151 case SPELL_SCHOOL_SHADOW:
152 spellId = SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_SHADOW;
153 break;
154 case SPELL_SCHOOL_ARCANE:
155 spellId = SPELL_GEN_ADAPTIVE_WARDING_ARCANE;
156 break;
157 default:
158 return;
159 }
160 GetTarget()->CastSpell(GetTarget(), spellId, true, NULL, aurEff);
161 }
162
163 void Register() override
164 {
165 DoCheckProc += AuraCheckProcFn(spell_gen_adaptive_warding_AuraScript::CheckProc);
166 OnEffectProc += AuraEffectProcFn(spell_gen_adaptive_warding_AuraScript::HandleProc, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_DUMMY);
167 }
168 };
169
170 AuraScript* GetAuraScript() const override
171 {
172 return new spell_gen_adaptive_warding_AuraScript();
173 }

182// 17619 - Alchemist Stone
183class spell_gen_alchemist_stone : public SpellScriptLoader
184{
185 public:
186 spell_gen_alchemist_stone() : SpellScriptLoader("spell_gen_alchemist_stone") { }
187
188 class spell_gen_alchemist_stone_AuraScript : public AuraScript
189 {
190 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_alchemist_stone_AuraScript);
191
192 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
193 {
194 if (!sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(ALECHEMIST_STONE_HEAL) ||
195 !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(ALECHEMIST_STONE_MANA))
196 return false;
197 return true;
198 }
199
200 bool CheckProc(ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
201 {
202 return eventInfo.GetDamageInfo()->GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_POTION;
203 }
204
205 void HandleProc(AuraEffect const* aurEff, ProcEventInfo& eventInfo)
206 {
207 PreventDefaultAction();
208
209 uint32 spellId = 0;
210 int32 bp = int32(eventInfo.GetDamageInfo()->GetDamage() * 0.4f);
211
212 if (eventInfo.GetDamageInfo()->GetSpellInfo()->HasEffect(DIFFICULTY_NONE, SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL))
213 spellId = ALECHEMIST_STONE_HEAL;
214 else if (eventInfo.GetDamageInfo()->GetSpellInfo()->HasEffect(DIFFICULTY_NONE, SPELL_EFFECT_ENERGIZE))
215 spellId = ALECHEMIST_STONE_MANA;
216
217 if (!spellId)
218 return;
219
220 GetTarget()->CastCustomSpell(spellId, SPELLVALUE_BASE_POINT0, bp, GetTarget(), true, NULL, aurEff);
221 }
222
223
224 void Register() override
225 {
226 DoCheckProc += AuraCheckProcFn(spell_gen_alchemist_stone_AuraScript::CheckProc);
227 OnEffectProc += AuraEffectProcFn(spell_gen_alchemist_stone_AuraScript::HandleProc, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_DUMMY);
228 }
229 };
230
231 AuraScript* GetAuraScript() const override
232 {
233 return new spell_gen_alchemist_stone_AuraScript();
234 }

276 class spell_gen_animal_blood_AuraScript : public AuraScript
277 {
278 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_animal_blood_AuraScript);
279
280 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
281 {
282 if (!sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(SPELL_SPAWN_BLOOD_POOL))
283 return false;
284 return true;
285 }
286
287 void OnApply(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
288 {
289 // Remove all auras with spell id 46221, except the one currently being applied
290 while (Aura* aur = GetUnitOwner()->GetOwnedAura(SPELL_ANIMAL_BLOOD, ObjectGuid::Empty, ObjectGuid::Empty, 0, GetAura()))
291 GetUnitOwner()->RemoveOwnedAura(aur);
292 }
293
294 void OnRemove(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
295 {
296 if (Unit* owner = GetUnitOwner())
297 if (owner->IsInWater())
298 owner->CastSpell(owner, SPELL_SPAWN_BLOOD_POOL, true);
299 }
300
301 void Register() override
302 {
303 AfterEffectApply += AuraEffectRemoveFn(spell_gen_animal_blood_AuraScript::OnApply, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL);
304 AfterEffectRemove += AuraEffectRemoveFn(spell_gen_animal_blood_AuraScript::OnRemove, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL);
305 }
306 };

502class spell_gen_bonked : public SpellScriptLoader
503{
504 public:
505 spell_gen_bonked() : SpellScriptLoader("spell_gen_bonked") { }
506
507 class spell_gen_bonked_SpellScript : public SpellScript
508 {
509 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_bonked_SpellScript);
510
511 void HandleScript(SpellEffIndex /*effIndex*/)
512 {
513 if (Player* target = GetHitPlayer())
514 {
515 Aura const* aura = GetHitAura();
516 if (!(aura && aura->GetStackAmount() == 3))
517 return;
518
519 target->CastSpell(target, SPELL_FOAM_SWORD_DEFEAT, true);
520 target->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(SPELL_BONKED);
521
522 if (Aura const* auraOnGuard = target->GetAura(SPELL_ON_GUARD))
523 {
524 if (Item* item = target->GetItemByGuid(auraOnGuard->GetCastItemGUID()))
525 target->DestroyItemCount(item->GetEntry(), 1, true);
526 }
527 }
528 }
529
530 void Register() override
531 {
532 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_bonked_SpellScript::HandleScript, EFFECT_1, SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT);
533 }
534 };

537 {
538 return new spell_gen_bonked_SpellScript();

542/* DOCUMENTATION: Break-Shield spells
543 Break-Shield spells can be classified in three groups:
544
545 - Spells on vehicle bar used by players:
546 + EFFECT_0: SCRIPT_EFFECT
547 + EFFECT_1: NONE
548 + EFFECT_2: NONE
549 - Spells cast by players triggered by script:
550 + EFFECT_0: SCHOOL_DAMAGE
551 + EFFECT_1: SCRIPT_EFFECT
552 + EFFECT_2: FORCE_CAST
553 - Spells cast by NPCs on players:
554 + EFFECT_0: SCHOOL_DAMAGE
555 + EFFECT_1: SCRIPT_EFFECT
556 + EFFECT_2: NONE
557
558 In the following script we handle the SCRIPT_EFFECT for effIndex EFFECT_0 and EFFECT_1.
559 - When handling EFFECT_0 we're in the "Spells on vehicle bar used by players" case
560 and we'll trigger "Spells cast by players triggered by script"
561 - When handling EFFECT_1 we're in the "Spells cast by players triggered by script"
562 or "Spells cast by NPCs on players" so we'll search for the first defend layer and drop it.
563*/
564
565enum BreakShieldSpells
566{
567 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_DAMAGE_2K = 62626,
568 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_DAMAGE_10K = 64590,
569
570 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_FACTION_MOUNTS = 62575, // Also on ToC5 mounts
571 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_CAMPAING_WARHORSE = 64595,
572 SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_UNK = 66480
573};
574
575class spell_gen_break_shield: public SpellScriptLoader
576{
577 public:
578 spell_gen_break_shield(const char* name) : SpellScriptLoader(name) { }
579
580 class spell_gen_break_shield_SpellScript : public SpellScript
581 {
582 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_break_shield_SpellScript);
583
584 void HandleScriptEffect(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
585 {
586 Unit* target = GetHitUnit();
587
588 switch (effIndex)
589 {
590 case EFFECT_0: // On spells wich trigger the damaging spell (and also the visual)
591 {
592 uint32 spellId;
593
594 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Id)
595 {
596 case SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_UNK:
597 case SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_CAMPAING_WARHORSE:
598 spellId = SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_DAMAGE_10K;
599 break;
600 case SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_TRIGGER_FACTION_MOUNTS:
601 spellId = SPELL_BREAK_SHIELD_DAMAGE_2K;
602 break;
603 default:
604 return;
605 }
606
607 if (Unit* rider = GetCaster()->GetCharmer())
608 rider->CastSpell(target, spellId, false);
609 else
610 GetCaster()->CastSpell(target, spellId, false);
611 break;
612 }
613 case EFFECT_1: // On damaging spells, for removing a defend layer
614 {
615 Unit::AuraApplicationMap const& auras = target->GetAppliedAuras();
616 for (Unit::AuraApplicationMap::const_iterator itr = auras.begin(); itr != auras.end(); ++itr)
617 {
618 if (Aura* aura = itr->second->GetBase())
619 {
620 SpellInfo const* auraInfo = aura->GetSpellInfo();
621 if (auraInfo && auraInfo->SpellIconID == 2007 && aura->HasEffectType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_TAKEN))
622 {
623 aura->ModStackAmount(-1, AURA_REMOVE_BY_ENEMY_SPELL);
624 // Remove dummys from rider (Necessary for updating visual shields)
625 if (Unit* rider = target->GetCharmer())
626 if (Aura* defend = rider->GetAura(aura->GetId()))
627 defend->ModStackAmount(-1, AURA_REMOVE_BY_ENEMY_SPELL);
628 break;
629 }
630 }
631 }
632 break;
633 }
634 default:
635 break;
636 }
637 }
638
639 void Register() override
640 {
641 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_break_shield_SpellScript::HandleScriptEffect, EFFECT_FIRST_FOUND, SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT);
642 }
643 };
644
645 SpellScript* GetSpellScript() const override
646 {
647 return new spell_gen_break_shield_SpellScript();
648 }
649};

679// 48750 - Burning Depths Necrolyte Image
680class spell_gen_burning_depths_necrolyte_image : public SpellScriptLoader
681{
682 public:
683 spell_gen_burning_depths_necrolyte_image() : SpellScriptLoader("spell_gen_burning_depths_necrolyte_image") { }
684
685 class spell_gen_burning_depths_necrolyte_image_AuraScript : public AuraScript
686 {
687 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_burning_depths_necrolyte_image_AuraScript);
688
689 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* spellInfo) override
690 {

897
898 class spell_gen_clone_weapon_auraScript : public AuraScript
899 {
900 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_clone_weapon_auraScript);
901
902 public:
903 spell_gen_clone_weapon_auraScript()
904 {
905 prevItem = 0;
906 }
907
908 private:
909 bool Validate(SpellInfo const* /*spellInfo*/) override
910 {
911 if (!sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_AURA) ||
912 !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_2_AURA) ||
913 !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_3_AURA) ||
914 !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(SPELL_COPY_OFFHAND_AURA) ||
915 !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(SPELL_COPY_OFFHAND_2_AURA) ||
916 !sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(SPELL_COPY_RANGED_AURA))
917 return false;
918 return true;
919 }
920
921 void OnApply(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
922 {
923 Unit* caster = GetCaster();
924 Unit* target = GetTarget();
925 if (!caster)
926 return;
927
928 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Id)
929 {
930 case SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_AURA:
931 case SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_2_AURA:
932 case SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_3_AURA:
933 {
934 prevItem = target->GetVirtualItemId(0);
935
936 if (Player* player = caster->ToPlayer())
937 {
938 if (Item* mainItem = player->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND))
939 target->SetVirtualItem(0, mainItem->GetEntry());
940 }
941 else
942 target->SetVirtualItem(0, caster->GetVirtualItemId(0));
943 break;
944 }
945 case SPELL_COPY_OFFHAND_AURA:
946 case SPELL_COPY_OFFHAND_2_AURA:
947 {
948 prevItem = target->GetVirtualItemId(1);
949
950 if (Player* player = caster->ToPlayer())
951 {
952 if (Item* offItem = player->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_OFFHAND))
953 target->SetVirtualItem(1, offItem->GetEntry());
954 }
955 else
956 target->SetVirtualItem(1, caster->GetVirtualItemId(1));
957 break;
958 }
959 case SPELL_COPY_RANGED_AURA:
960 {
961 prevItem = target->GetVirtualItemId(2);
962
963 if (Player* player = caster->ToPlayer())
964 {
965 if (Item* rangedItem = player->GetItemByPos(INVENTORY_SLOT_BAG_0, EQUIPMENT_SLOT_MAINHAND))
966 target->SetVirtualItem(2, rangedItem->GetEntry());
967 }
968 else
969 target->SetVirtualItem(2, caster->GetVirtualItemId(2));
970 break;
971 }
972 default:
973 break;
974 }
975 }
976
977 void OnRemove(AuraEffect const* /*aurEff*/, AuraEffectHandleModes /*mode*/)
978 {
979 Unit* target = GetTarget();
980
981 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Id)
982 {
983 case SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_AURA:
984 case SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_2_AURA:
985 case SPELL_COPY_WEAPON_3_AURA:
986 target->SetVirtualItem(0, prevItem);
987 break;
988 case SPELL_COPY_OFFHAND_AURA:
989 case SPELL_COPY_OFFHAND_2_AURA:
990 target->SetVirtualItem(1, prevItem);
991 break;
992 case SPELL_COPY_RANGED_AURA:
993 target->SetVirtualItem(2, prevItem);
994 break;
995 default:
996 break;
997 }
998 }
999
1000 void Register() override
1001 {
1002 OnEffectApply += AuraEffectApplyFn(spell_gen_clone_weapon_auraScript::OnApply, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DUMMY, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL_OR_REAPPLY_MASK);
1003 OnEffectRemove += AuraEffectRemoveFn(spell_gen_clone_weapon_auraScript::OnRemove, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DUMMY, AURA_EFFECT_HANDLE_REAL_OR_REAPPLY_MASK);
1004 }
1005
1006 private:
1007 uint32 prevItem;
1008 };
1009
1010 AuraScript* GetAuraScript() const override
1011 {
1012 return new spell_gen_clone_weapon_auraScript();
1013 }

1633 {
1634 PrepareAuraScript(spell_gen_gift_of_naaru_AuraScript);
1635
1636 void CalculateAmount(AuraEffect const* aurEff, int32& amount, bool& /*canBeRecalculated*/)
1637 {
1638 if (!GetCaster())
1639 return;
1640
1641 float heal = 0.0f;
1642 switch (GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName)
1643 {
1644 case SPELLFAMILY_MAGE:
1645 case SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK:
1646 case SPELLFAMILY_PRIEST:
1647 heal = 1.885f * float(GetCaster()->SpellBaseDamageBonusDone(GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask()));
1648 break;
1649 case SPELLFAMILY_PALADIN:
1650 case SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN:
1651 heal = std::max(1.885f * float(GetCaster()->SpellBaseDamageBonusDone(GetSpellInfo()->GetSchoolMask())), 1.1f * float(GetCaster()->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK)));
1652 break;
1653 case SPELLFAMILY_WARRIOR:
1654 case SPELLFAMILY_HUNTER:
1655 case SPELLFAMILY_DEATHKNIGHT:
1656 heal = 1.1f * float(std::max(GetCaster()->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK), GetCaster()->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(RANGED_ATTACK)));
1657 break;
1658 case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
1659 default:
1660 break;
1661 }
1662
1663 int32 healTick = std::floor(heal / aurEff->GetTotalTicks());
1664 amount += int32(std::max(healTick, 0));
1665 }
1666
1667 void Register() override
1668 {
1669 DoEffectCalcAmount += AuraEffectCalcAmountFn(spell_gen_gift_of_naaru_AuraScript::CalculateAmount, EFFECT_0, SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL);
1670 }

1846/* DOCUMENTATION: Charge spells
1847 Charge spells can be classified in four groups:
1848
1849 - Spells on vehicle bar used by players:
1850 + EFFECT_0: SCRIPT_EFFECT
1851 + EFFECT_1: TRIGGER_SPELL
1852 + EFFECT_2: NONE
1853 - Spells cast by player's mounts triggered by script:
1854 + EFFECT_0: CHARGE
1855 + EFFECT_1: TRIGGER_SPELL
1856 + EFFECT_2: APPLY_AURA
1857 - Spells cast by players on the target triggered by script:
1858 + EFFECT_0: SCHOOL_DAMAGE
1859 + EFFECT_1: SCRIPT_EFFECT
1860 + EFFECT_2: NONE
1861 - Spells cast by NPCs on players:
1862 + EFFECT_0: SCHOOL_DAMAGE
1863 + EFFECT_1: CHARGE
1864 + EFFECT_2: SCRIPT_EFFECT
1865
1866 In the following script we handle the SCRIPT_EFFECT and CHARGE
1867 - When handling SCRIPT_EFFECT:
1868 + EFFECT_0: Corresponds to "Spells on vehicle bar used by players" and we make player's mount cast
1869 the charge effect on the current target ("Spells cast by player's mounts triggered by script").
1870 + EFFECT_1 and EFFECT_2: Triggered when "Spells cast by player's mounts triggered by script" hits target,
1871 corresponding to "Spells cast by players on the target triggered by script" and "Spells cast by
1872 NPCs on players" and we check Defend layers and drop a charge of the first found.
1873 - When handling CHARGE:
1874 + Only launched for "Spells cast by player's mounts triggered by script", makes the player cast the
1875 damaging spell on target with a small chance of failing it.
1876*/
1877
1878enum ChargeSpells
1879{
1880 SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_8K5 = 62874,
1881 SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_20K = 68498,
1882 SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_45K = 64591,
1883
1884 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_8K5 = 63661,
1885 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_20K_1 = 68284,
1886 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_20K_2 = 68501,
1887 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_45K_1 = 62563,
1888 SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_45K_2 = 66481,
1889
1890 SPELL_CHARGE_TRIGGER_FACTION_MOUNTS = 62960,
1891 SPELL_CHARGE_TRIGGER_TRIAL_CHAMPION = 68282,
1892
1893 SPELL_CHARGE_MISS_EFFECT = 62977,
1894};
1895
1896class spell_gen_mounted_charge: public SpellScriptLoader
1897{
1898 public:
1899 spell_gen_mounted_charge() : SpellScriptLoader("spell_gen_mounted_charge") { }
1900
1901 class spell_gen_mounted_charge_SpellScript : public SpellScript
1902 {
1903 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_mounted_charge_SpellScript);
1904
1905 void HandleScriptEffect(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
1906 {
1907 Unit* target = GetHitUnit();
1908
1909 switch (effIndex)
1910 {
1911 case EFFECT_0: // On spells wich trigger the damaging spell (and also the visual)
1912 {
1913 uint32 spellId;
1914
1915 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Id)
1916 {
1917 case SPELL_CHARGE_TRIGGER_TRIAL_CHAMPION:
1918 spellId = SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_20K_1;
1919 break;
1920 case SPELL_CHARGE_TRIGGER_FACTION_MOUNTS:
1921 spellId = SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_8K5;
1922 break;
1923 default:
1924 return;
1925 }
1926
1927 // If target isn't a training dummy there's a chance of failing the charge
1928 if (!target->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_DISABLE_MOVE) && roll_chance_f(12.5f))
1929 spellId = SPELL_CHARGE_MISS_EFFECT;
1930
1931 if (Unit* vehicle = GetCaster()->GetVehicleBase())
1932 vehicle->CastSpell(target, spellId, false);
1933 else
1934 GetCaster()->CastSpell(target, spellId, false);
1935 break;
1936 }
1937 case EFFECT_1: // On damaging spells, for removing a defend layer
1938 case EFFECT_2:
1939 {
1940 Unit::AuraApplicationMap const& auras = target->GetAppliedAuras();
1941 for (Unit::AuraApplicationMap::const_iterator itr = auras.begin(); itr != auras.end(); ++itr)
1942 {
1943 if (Aura* aura = itr->second->GetBase())
1944 {
1945 SpellInfo const* auraInfo = aura->GetSpellInfo();
1946 if (auraInfo && auraInfo->SpellIconID == 2007 && aura->HasEffectType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_TAKEN))
1947 {
1948 aura->ModStackAmount(-1, AURA_REMOVE_BY_ENEMY_SPELL);
1949 // Remove dummys from rider (Necessary for updating visual shields)
1950 if (Unit* rider = target->GetCharmer())
1951 if (Aura* defend = rider->GetAura(aura->GetId()))
1952 defend->ModStackAmount(-1, AURA_REMOVE_BY_ENEMY_SPELL);
1953 break;
1954 }
1955 }
1956 }
1957 break;
1958 }
1959 default:
1960 break;
1961 }
1962 }
1963
1964 void HandleChargeEffect(SpellEffIndex /*effIndex*/)
1965 {
1966 uint32 spellId;
1967
1968 switch (GetSpellInfo()->Id)
1969 {
1970 case SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_8K5:
1971 spellId = SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_8K5;
1972 break;
1973 case SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_20K_1:
1974 case SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_20K_2:
1975 spellId = SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_20K;
1976 break;
1977 case SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_45K_1:
1978 case SPELL_CHARGE_CHARGING_EFFECT_45K_2:
1979 spellId = SPELL_CHARGE_DAMAGE_45K;
1980 break;
1981 default:
1982 return;
1983 }
1984
1985 if (Unit* rider = GetCaster()->GetCharmer())
1986 rider->CastSpell(GetHitUnit(), spellId, false);
1987 else
1988 GetCaster()->CastSpell(GetHitUnit(), spellId, false);
1989 }
1990
1991 void Register() override
1992 {
1993 SpellInfo const* spell = sSpellMgr->AssertSpellInfo(m_scriptSpellId);
1994
1995 if (spell->HasEffect(DIFFICULTY_NONE, SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT))
1996 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_mounted_charge_SpellScript::HandleScriptEffect, EFFECT_FIRST_FOUND, SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT);
1997
1998 if (spell->GetEffect(EFFECT_0)->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_CHARGE)
1999 OnEffectHitTarget += SpellEffectFn(spell_gen_mounted_charge_SpellScript::HandleChargeEffect, EFFECT_0, SPELL_EFFECT_CHARGE);
2000 }
2001 };
2002
2003 SpellScript* GetSpellScript() const override
2004 {
2005 return new spell_gen_mounted_charge_SpellScript();
2006 }

2767 {
2768 PrepareSpellScript(spell_gen_replenishment_SpellScript);
2769
2770 void RemoveInvalidTargets(std::list<WorldObject*>& targets)
2771 {
2772 // In arenas Replenishment may only affect the caster
2773 if (Player* caster = GetCaster()->ToPlayer())
2774 {
2775 if (caster->InArena())
2776 {
2777 targets.clear();
2778 targets.push_back(caster);
2779 return;
2780 }
2781 }
2782
2783 targets.remove_if(ReplenishmentCheck());
2784
2785 uint8 const maxTargets = 10;
2786
2787 if (targets.size() > maxTargets)
2788 {
2789 targets.sort(Trinity::PowerPctOrderPred(POWER_MANA));
2790 targets.resize(maxTargets);
2791 }
2792 }

2795 {
2796 OnObjectAreaTargetSelect += SpellObjectAreaTargetSelectFn(spell_gen_replenishment_SpellScript::RemoveInvalidTargets, EFFECT_ALL, TARGET_UNIT_CASTER_AREA_RAID);
